@page "/help/faq"
@attribute [Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.Authorize(Policy = "InstitutionUser")]

<PageTitle>FAQ — Help Center — FC Engine Portal</PageTitle>

<HelpLayout>
    <div class="help-article">
        <h2 class="help-article-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p class="help-article-intro">
            Find answers to commonly asked questions about the FC Engine FI Portal.
        </p>

        <!-- Account & Access -->
        <section id="account">
            <h3 class="help-faq-category">Account &amp; Access</h3>

            <AccordionPanel Title="How do I change my password?">
                <p>
                    Click on your profile avatar in the sidebar, then select <strong>Settings</strong>,
                    or navigate directly to <a href="/settings">Account Settings</a>.
                    Enter your current password, then your new password twice to confirm.
                </p>
                <p>Password requirements:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Minimum 8 characters</li>
                    <li>At least one uppercase letter</li>
                    <li>At least one lowercase letter</li>
                    <li>At least one number</li>
                    <li>At least one special character</li>
                </ul>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="I forgot my password. How do I reset it?">
                <p>
                    On the login page, click <strong>"Forgot password?"</strong>. Enter the email address
                    associated with your account. You'll receive a password reset link via email.
                    If you don't receive the email, contact your institution administrator.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="What are the different user roles?">
                <p>The portal supports four roles:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Admin</strong> — Full access. Can manage users, institution settings, and all portal features.</li>
                    <li><strong>Maker</strong> — Can create, prepare, and submit returns. Cannot approve their own submissions when Maker-Checker is enabled.</li>
                    <li><strong>Checker</strong> — Can review and approve/reject submissions made by Makers. Can also submit returns.</li>
                    <li><strong>Viewer</strong> — Read-only access. Can view submissions, reports, and templates but cannot submit or approve.</li>
                </ul>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="How do I add new users to my institution?">
                <p>
                    Only institution Admins can manage users. Navigate to
                    <a href="/institution/team">Team Members</a> from the Account section in the sidebar.
                    Click <strong>Add User</strong>, fill in the user details, and assign a role.
                    The new user will receive a temporary password that must be changed on first login.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>
        </section>

        <!-- Submission -->
        <section id="submission">
            <h3 class="help-faq-category">Submissions</h3>

            <AccordionPanel Title="How do I submit a return?">
                <p>
                    Navigate to <a href="/submit">Submit Return</a>, select a template and reporting period,
                    then either upload your XML file or fill in the online form.
                    See the <a href="/help/submission-guide">Submission Guide</a> for detailed instructions.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="Can I submit the same return twice for the same period?">
                <p>
                    You can only have one active submission per template per reporting period.
                    If you need to correct a previously submitted return, you must re-submit it,
                    which will replace the previous submission.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If a submission was rejected (by validation or by a Checker), you can re-submit
                    from the submission details page, and the new submission will be linked to the original.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="What file formats are accepted?">
                <p>
                    The portal accepts XML files only. Your XML must conform to the XSD schema
                    for the specific return template. Download schemas from the
                    <a href="/schemas">Download Schemas</a> page.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Alternatively, you can use the <strong>online form</strong> to enter data directly
                    without preparing an XML file.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="How do I check the status of my submissions?">
                <p>
                    Go to <a href="/submissions">My Submissions</a> to see all your submissions
                    with their current status:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Accepted</strong> — Successfully validated and stored</li>
                    <li><strong>Accepted with Warnings</strong> — Stored but has warnings to review</li>
                    <li><strong>Rejected</strong> — Failed validation, needs correction</li>
                    <li><strong>Pending Approval</strong> — Awaiting Checker approval</li>
                    <li><strong>Approval Rejected</strong> — Rejected by Checker, needs re-submission</li>
                </ul>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="What is the maximum file size for XML uploads?">
                <p>
                    The maximum file size for XML uploads is <strong>10 MB</strong>.
                    Most returns are well under this limit. If your file exceeds this size,
                    check for unnecessary whitespace or formatting in your XML.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>
        </section>

        <!-- Validation -->
        <section id="validation">
            <h3 class="help-faq-category">Validation</h3>

            <AccordionPanel Title="My submission was rejected with validation errors. What do I do?">
                <p>
                    Open the submission details to view the full validation report. Each error will show:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>The validation category (Schema, TypeRange, IntraSheet, etc.)</li>
                    <li>The specific field(s) involved</li>
                    <li>The expected vs actual values</li>
                    <li>A description of the issue</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    Fix the issues in your XML file and re-submit.
                    See the <a href="/help/validation-errors">Validation Error Guide</a> for detailed explanations.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="What is the difference between an error and a warning?">
                <p>
                    <strong>Errors</strong> prevent your submission from being accepted. You must fix all errors.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Warnings</strong> are informational — they flag potential issues but don't prevent acceptance.
                    Your submission will be accepted with an "Accepted with Warnings" status.
                    You should review warnings but don't necessarily need to re-submit.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="Why does my sum formula fail even though my numbers look correct?">
                <p>
                    Formula validation uses a tolerance mechanism. Most sum formulas allow a small
                    tolerance (e.g., ±0.01 or ±0.5%) to account for rounding differences.
                    If your difference exceeds the tolerance, it will be flagged.
                </p>
                <p>Common causes:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Rounding errors — ensure all amounts are rounded consistently</li>
                    <li>Missing component — check that all items in the sum are included</li>
                    <li>Sign errors — verify negative values use the minus sign correctly</li>
                </ul>
            </AccordionPanel>
        </section>

        <!-- Approvals -->
        <section id="approvals">
            <h3 class="help-faq-category">Approvals (Maker-Checker)</h3>

            <AccordionPanel Title="What is Maker-Checker?">
                <p>
                    Maker-Checker is a dual-approval workflow where one user (the Maker) prepares and submits
                    a return, and another user (the Checker) reviews and approves or rejects it.
                    This provides an additional layer of quality control.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Your institution Admin can enable or disable Maker-Checker in
                    <a href="/institution/settings">Institution Settings</a>.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="Can I approve my own submission?">
                <p>
                    No. The Maker and Checker must be different users. If you submitted a return,
                    someone else with the Checker or Admin role must approve it.
                    This is a security control that cannot be overridden.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="How do I approve a pending submission?">
                <p>
                    If you have the Checker or Admin role, navigate to
                    <a href="/approvals">Pending Approvals</a> from the sidebar.
                    You'll see all submissions awaiting approval. Click on a submission to review
                    the validation report and data, then click <strong>Approve</strong> or <strong>Reject</strong>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Rejections require a comment explaining the reason, so the Maker knows what to fix.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="What happens when a submission is rejected by a Checker?">
                <p>
                    The submission status changes to <strong>Approval Rejected</strong>.
                    The Maker receives a notification with the Checker's comments.
                    The Maker can then re-submit a corrected return, which will be linked to the
                    original submission for audit trail purposes.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>
        </section>

        <!-- Technical -->
        <section id="technical">
            <h3 class="help-faq-category">Technical</h3>

            <AccordionPanel Title="Which browsers are supported?">
                <p>The FC Engine Portal supports the following browsers:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Google Chrome (latest 2 versions)</li>
                    <li>Microsoft Edge (latest 2 versions)</li>
                    <li>Mozilla Firefox (latest 2 versions)</li>
                    <li>Safari (latest 2 versions)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>JavaScript must be enabled for the portal to function properly.</p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="How do I generate XML from my spreadsheet?">
                <p>
                    If you maintain your return data in Excel or another spreadsheet:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Download the XSD schema for your template from the <a href="/schemas">Schemas</a> page</li>
                    <li>Map your spreadsheet columns to the XML element names defined in the schema</li>
                    <li>Use a tool like Excel XML mapping, Python, or any XML generation library to produce the XML</li>
                    <li>Validate the generated XML against the XSD before uploading</li>
                </ol>
                <p>
                    Alternatively, use the <strong>online form</strong> to enter data directly from your spreadsheet
                    without generating XML.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="Is there an API for automated submissions?">
                <p>
                    Yes, the FC Engine provides a REST API for automated XML submissions.
                    Contact your CBN representative for API access credentials and documentation.
                    The API endpoint accepts XML files and returns validation results in JSON format.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>
        </section>

        <!-- Compliance -->
        <section id="compliance">
            <h3 class="help-faq-category">Compliance &amp; Deadlines</h3>

            <AccordionPanel Title="What are the submission deadlines?">
                <p>
                    Submission deadlines vary by return template and frequency (Monthly, Quarterly, Annually).
                    Check the <a href="/calendar">Reporting Calendar</a> for upcoming deadlines.
                </p>
                <p>
                    You'll also receive notifications when deadlines are approaching (if enabled in your institution settings).
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="What happens if I miss a deadline?">
                <p>
                    Late submissions may be flagged by CBN and could result in regulatory consequences.
                    If you're unable to submit on time, contact CBN support as soon as possible.
                    The portal still allows submissions after the deadline unless the reporting period
                    has been explicitly closed.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>

            <AccordionPanel Title="How long are submissions retained?">
                <p>
                    All submissions and their validation reports are retained indefinitely for regulatory
                    audit purposes. You can view historical submissions in
                    <a href="/submissions">My Submissions</a>.
                </p>
            </AccordionPanel>
        </section>
    </div>
</HelpLayout>
